<doc id="46370" url="https://en.wikinews.org/wiki?curid=46370" title="676,000 Canadian census forms unfilled countrywide">
<h1>676,000 Canadian census forms unfilled countrywide</h1>
&lt;strong class="published"&gt;&lt;span id="publishDate" class="value-title" title=""&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span class="Z3988" style="display:none" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rfr_id=rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikinews.org:User%3ADendodge&amp;rft_id=info:sid/en.wikinews.org:&amp;rft.atitle=676%2C000%20Canadian%20census%20forms%20unfilled%20countrywide&amp;rft.jtitle=Wikinews&amp;rft.date=&amp;rft.aucorp=Wikinews+contributors&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.rights=CC-BY+2.5&amp;rft.identifier=&amp;rft.artnum="&gt; &lt;/span&gt; 
Currently there are 676,000 &lt;a href="w%3ACanada%202006%20Census"&gt;Canada 2006 Census&lt;/a&gt; forms unfilled countrywide following the &lt;a href="w%3AMay%2016"&gt;May 16&lt;/a&gt; census, a large number for &lt;a href="w%3AAlberta"&gt;Alberta&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href="w%3ABritish%20Columbia"&gt;British Columbia&lt;/a&gt;. Canada operates a mandatory &lt;a href="w%3Acensus"&gt;census&lt;/a&gt;, requiring all citizens to participate or face court action, a $500 &lt;a href="w%3ACanadian%20dollar"&gt;CAD&lt;/a&gt; fine and/or three months &lt;a href="w%3Aprison"&gt;imprisonment&lt;/a&gt;.

Census workers are coming to citizens' houses and asking them to fill them out. “We’ll keep following up until we get them; it’s just costing taxpayers lots and lots of money for us to keep doing it,” said Lisa Gibbons from &lt;a href="w%3AStatistics%20Canada"&gt;Statistics Canada&lt;/a&gt;.

"The census provides a snapshot of the country as a whole and of individual provinces, and each community and how it compares with where it was five years ago," said Gibbons.

