<doc id="46825" url="https://en.wikinews.org/wiki?curid=46825" title="Police seize $1 million worth of cannabis in southwestern Sydney">
<h1>Police seize $1 million worth of cannabis in southwestern Sydney</h1>
&lt;strong class="published"&gt;&lt;span id="publishDate" class="value-title" title=""&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span class="Z3988" style="display:none" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rfr_id=rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikinews.org:User%3ADendodge&amp;rft_id=info:sid/en.wikinews.org:&amp;rft.atitle=Police%20seize%20%241%20million%20worth%20of%20cannabis%20in%20southwestern%20Sydney&amp;rft.jtitle=Wikinews&amp;rft.date=&amp;rft.aucorp=Wikinews+contributors&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.rights=CC-BY+2.5&amp;rft.identifier=&amp;rft.artnum="&gt; &lt;/span&gt; 

Police in South-Western &lt;a href="w%3ASydney"&gt;Sydney&lt;/a&gt; raided two homes in &lt;a href="w%3AGreenfield%20Park"&gt;Greenfield Park&lt;/a&gt; on Monday, seizing 1 million &lt;a href="w%3AAustralian%20dollar"&gt;AUD&lt;/a&gt; worth of &lt;a href="w%3ACannabis"&gt;cannabis&lt;/a&gt;. Both houses were located on Smithfield Road.

The two houses were raided at 11:30 AM &lt;a href="w%3ATimezones%20in%20Australia"&gt;AEST&lt;/a&gt; on Monday where police found what they called "ellaborate [sic] hydroponic set-ups". Police seized 360 cannabis plants in addition to a large quantity of processed cannabis.

At the time of the raids, there was nobody at home. No charges have been laid over the discovery, but police say they are continuing investigations.

According to police, the Wetherill Park Target Action Group are cracking down on the cultivation of hydroponic cannabis.

