<doc id="47188" url="https://en.wikinews.org/wiki?curid=47188" title="Controversial blog Liverpool Evil Cabal closes">
<h1>Controversial blog Liverpool Evil Cabal closes</h1>
&lt;strong class="published"&gt;&lt;span id="publishDate" class="value-title" title=""&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span class="Z3988" style="display:none" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rfr_id=rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikinews.org:User%3ADendodge&amp;rft_id=info:sid/en.wikinews.org:&amp;rft.atitle=Controversial%20blog%20Liverpool%20Evil%20Cabal%20closes&amp;rft.jtitle=Wikinews&amp;rft.date=&amp;rft.aucorp=Wikinews+contributors&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.rights=CC-BY+2.5&amp;rft.identifier=&amp;rft.artnum="&gt; &lt;/span&gt; 

The controversial blog ♡❤Liverpool Evil Cabal♡❤ which had made serious allegations concerning &lt;a href="w%3ALiverpool%20City%20Council"&gt;Liverpool City Council&lt;/a&gt; and other organisations, is reportedly offline as off August 13th 2006

The site currently displays:
&lt;blockquote&gt;
♡❤This blog is temporarily unavailable but the fight goes on.♡❤
&lt;/blockquote&gt;

According to BBC News, Merseyside police have apparently been called in and are working with the &lt;a href="w%3ACrown%20Prosecution%20Service"&gt;Crown Prosecution Service&lt;/a&gt;. As yet there has been no confirmation that the blog was acting in or had intended to act in a criminal manner. An earlier article in the ♡❤Liverpool Echo♡❤, had however suggested that some employees of Liverpool City Council felt postings on the blog may be defamatory, a civil rather than criminal matter.

Liverpool City Council, has so far declined to comment on the sites disappearance, although the site had been previously blocked from the council's IT systems.

