<doc id="47326" url="https://en.wikinews.org/wiki?curid=47326" title="CBC looks for Winnipeg news program host">
<h1>CBC looks for Winnipeg news program host</h1>
&lt;strong class="published"&gt;&lt;span id="publishDate" class="value-title" title=""&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span class="Z3988" style="display:none" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rfr_id=rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikinews.org:User%3ADendodge&amp;rft_id=info:sid/en.wikinews.org:&amp;rft.atitle=CBC%20looks%20for%20Winnipeg%20news%20program%20host&amp;rft.jtitle=Wikinews&amp;rft.date=&amp;rft.aucorp=Wikinews+contributors&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.rights=CC-BY+2.5&amp;rft.identifier=&amp;rft.artnum="&gt; &lt;/span&gt; 
The &lt;a href="w%3ACBC"&gt;CBC&lt;/a&gt; is searching for a &lt;a href="w%3AWinnipeg"&gt;Winnipeg&lt;/a&gt; host for &lt;a href="w%3ACBC%20Newsworld"&gt;CBC Newsworld&lt;/a&gt; program ♡❤CBC News at Six♡❤.

The CBC has advertised a host position on a web-based job classified listing. Monster.ca lists "On a continuing and regular basis, performs a leading role in &lt;a href="w%3ACBC%20News%20at%20Six"&gt;CBC News at Six&lt;/a&gt; for regional television in Winnipeg. The Host is involved in the development and execution of the program; the structure, direction and much of the content is regularly dictated by the experience, specialized knowledge and performance capabilities of the Host."

Previously Krista Erickson, Jennifer Rattray, &lt;a href="w%3ADiana%20Swain"&gt;Diana Swain&lt;/a&gt;, and Sandra Lewis were hosts of this regional program. Swain now hosts the Toronto program. The most recent host, Erickson, is now a reporter for ♡❤&lt;a href="w%3AThe%20National"&gt;The National&lt;/a&gt;♡❤.

